history.content:
I took 120 with Babak this past fall. Babak starts from the ground up, including LTI systems, so I wouldn't be too worried. If you feel the urge to review material though, from 16A I would make sure you have a solid understanding of inner products,vector spaces, and orthogonal bases. From 16B, complex numbers is probably the most important thing to know going in since, as stated before, Babak does review LTI systems. 

For outside resources, Babak suggests as an optional textbook Signals and Systems by Oppenheim, although from what I've heard from other students who did get the textbook, he doesn't follow its structure too closely. 

Usually its 3 midterms. When I took it, there were also 3 quizzes with one quiz drop, accounting for 15% of the grade.

Hello! I'm taking EE 120 this coming Spring semester with Babak. I have taken EE 16A/B, but don't feel too confident with the concepts of LTI systems, and DFT from 16B. To people who have taken 120, are there any resources that I can use to study these topics, besides the 16B website? Also, are there any other topics from 16A/B that are covered in 120 that are worth reviewing? By any chance, are these topics covered in 120 at all during the beginning?

Also, are there 3 midterms in the course or the usual 2 midterms and one final?

Thanks!
